I'm confused as to how the `forwardRef` polyfill in that patch changes anything at all in React 15. It's just the identity function. So before the patch, we had:

```jsx
function Link(props) {
  // ...
}

export { Link }
```

And after the patch we have:

```jsx
let forwardRef = C => C;

const Link = forwardRef((props, ref) => {
  // ...
})

export { Link }
```

All React 15 sees is a function that takes some props.

Is [this line](https://github.com/ReactTraining/react-router/commit/b5528ed63a1a26c7009669aa97acb0103312170e#diff-8c17f8f99262d24cba447ddc8f465455R76) the one that causes the breakage??
